Rating: 3
VERY good--with some modifications. Used 1/2 pound bacon, didn't get much flavor next time will try 1/2 ground beef and 1/2 ground pork instead. Added garlic and 2 onions which I sauted in the bacon grease. Added a small can of tomato paste. Added ranch season based on prior reviews however it didn't "make" the dish. What DID "make" the dish was adding about 3/4 bottle of beer (only had Miller Light, still good), really gave it a good broth, too but still a chunky chili. Added a handful of sliced jalapenos which gave it a nice kick, although too spicy for my 6 year old. Used 3 cans of beans, kidney and pinto. Could probably even use a 4th can as this dish is plenty meaty. I forgot to add some corn but that would have really been tasty. Only 3 forks because I added so much to it thanks to previous reviews. Agree that recipe as is doesn't really count as "cooking" (cans, season packets and whatnot) but it was perfect for a weeknight family dinner.

Rating: 3
