Rating: 3
I made this Chili for a church function and people couldn't stop coming up to me for the recipe. I used the recipe on the site as my "base" and then added the following: 1/2 lb. bacon (rather than just 1/4 lb.) 1 pkg. ranch seasoning (omit the chili seasoning in the recipe) 1 T. chopped garlic chili powder to taste ground red pepper to taste cayenne to taste I cooked the ground beef and then drained all but a very small amount in which I sauteed the onions and garlic. Then I threw everything in a crock pot, let sit overnight and slow cooked it the next day for 5-6 hours. Delicious!!

