Rating: 4
I make this chili often. It's fast, easy, and kids love it. So do picky adults and people who won't usually eat chili. I have modified the recipe and run the risk of being accused of not using this recipe at all, but it's the same--just different. We don't do pork so I use a bit of olive oil instead and start the recipe from the place where you brown the beef. I drain the fat off then use plain, not Italian tomatoes and regular canned pinto bean. Instead of the seasoning mix I use 1 tablespoon chili powder and 1/4-1/2 teaspoon cayenne.

