Rating: 1
This recipe is definitely for the hopeless cook. It's one step above opening up a can of store-bought chili. Where's the heat? The real trick to chili, as I've learned through trial & error, is to layer the hot stuff. That way you get a good burn, without overpowering from just one spice. So add a couple of different hot spices. If you make it too hot, just throw a dollop of sour cream or some grated cheese on top. And chili, like soup, always tastes better the next day.

